        "Lower Men"
      ],
      "registrationUrl": "http://bit.ly/fvbl-2s-mw-rsvp-2",
      "format": "2s",
      "surface": "grass",
      "feeUSD": 60,
      "registrationDeadline": "2026-06-21",
      "description": "Power Doubles (Women's and Men's) — a Saturday grass doubles tournament hosted by FVBL (@fvbleague), the long-running Bay Area grass series that runs out of the Newark/Fremont area. Players sign up through the bit.ly RSVP form, which feeds directly to the organizers — that's the link to use, not the Facebook event. Format is standard FVBL doubles: shorter (2s) court, women's net height for the W division and men's height for M, pool play into a playoff bracket, one timeout per set, 5-minute warmups, and the usual FVBL hand rules (no open-hand passing on serve receive or rallies, set-overs only on 2nd/3rd touch and must be square, blocks don't count as a touch). Teams BYO whistle for reffing and BYO ball, shade, food, and water. Carpooling encouraged."
    },
