      },
      "divisions": [
        "Women's",
        "Men's"
      ],
      "registrationUrl": "http://bit.ly/fvbl-2s-mw-rsvp-3",
      "format": "2s",
      "surface": "grass",
      "description": "Summer Doubles (Women's and Men's) — a Saturday grass doubles event hosted by FVBL (@fvbleague) in the Newark/Fremont area of the Bay Area. RSVP through the bit.ly link; that form is the actual sign-up, the Facebook event is just the announcement. Same FVBL doubles format as the rest of the 2s slate: women's bracket plays at women's net height, men's at men's net height, shorter (2s) court, pool play into a playoff bracket. House rules: no open-hand passing on serve receive or rallies (open hand only on hard-driven hits), set-overs allowed only on 2nd/3rd touch and must be square, blocks don't count as a touch and can't redirect, one timeout per set, 5-minute warmups, late teams lose a point after 10 minutes and forfeit at 20. BYO whistle, ball, food, shade, and water; teams ref each other."
    },
